Q. UnitedHealth Group (UHG) has a program called Advocate4Me, which allows policy holders (or, members) to call an advocate and receive support for their health care needs – whether that's claims and benefits support, drug coverage, pre- and post-authorisation, medical records, emergency assistance, or member portal services.
Write a query to find how many UHG policy holders made three, or more calls, assuming each call is identified by the case_id column.

A.
Method 1:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS POLICY_HOLDER_COUNT 
FROM (
  SELECT POLICY_HOLDER_ID FROM callers
  GROUP BY POLICY_HOLDER_ID
  HAVING COUNT(*) > 2
) t
;

Method 2: 
WITH COUNT_CALLERS AS
(SELECT POLICY_HOLDER_ID, CASE_ID,
ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY POLICY_HOLDER_ID) AS RN
FROM callers)

SELECT COUNT(*) AS POLICY_HOLDER_COUNT FROM COUNT_CALLERS
WHERE RN = 3

;
